<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RENDON GRANTED RELEASE FROM USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC kicker Adam Rendon, who has been suspended
since the spring, has been granted his release and will transfer to
another school.
</P>
<P>
   ``He asked for his transfer request and it was granted,'' USC
coach Paul Hackett said Monday. ``We said he could go.''
</P>
<P>
   Rendon was suspended for poor academic performance and because
he had missed several study sessions last spring. ``In Adam's case,
he has not done the things he needed to do to get reinstated,''
Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   The pair met after the start of the season, but Hackett made it
clear Rendon would probably never be brought back onto the team.
</P>
<P>
   Rendon, who is believed to be interested in transferring to a
Western Athletic Conference school, will have one year of
eligibility remaining. He handled kickoffs for the Trojans and was
0 for 2 on field goals last season.
</P>
<P>
   Harris in doubt: Tight end Antoine Harris, who has been bothered
by a recurring sprained ankle injury, will probably be ``limited''
against Florida State, according to Hackett. Harris, who injured
the ankle against San Diego State, did not play last week against
Oregon State.
</P>
<P>
   Former quarterback John Fox will back up freshman Lonnie Ford if
Harris is unavailable.
</P>
<P>
   Three other injured starters _ linebacker Mark Cusano, strong
safety Grant Pearsall and defensive end Lawrence Larry _ are
expected to play.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said centers Eric Denmon (sprained ankle) and Matt
McShane (strained knee) are probably out for the game.
</P>
<P>
   Colossal spread: USC is listed as a 17{-point underdog to
Florida State. It is believed to be the largest margin the Trojans
have opened as an underdog in at least 15 years. USC was a 17-point
underdog last year against Washington and was also a 17-point
underdog against the Huskies in 1991.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
