   BRITISH-SHOPS (New York) _ If it is true, as Disraeli once said,
that the British are a nation of shopkeepers, why is it that they
can't seem to keep shop over here? Many British retailers have
tried their hand in the United States and failed, like Conran's
Habitat, a defunct housewares chain, and Next, a trendy clothing
store. Others made a splash initially but later struggled mightily,
most notably Laura Ashley and the Body Shop. The reasons are many,
ranging from Americans' obsession with bargains to a bevy of real
estate mistakes made by British retail companies to the sheer
vastness of the American marketplace. By Jennifer Steinhauer. (with
graphic)
