<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Encore! Encore!
 &HT;    By Kevin D. Thompson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When it debuts: Tuesday, 8:30 p.m., NBC.
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: A loud-mouthed, self-centered, skirt-chasing
opera star (Nathan Lane) loses his voice and returns to his
family-owned winery in Napa Valley.
</P>
<P>
   How is it? It bombs. Now we know why NBC hid this awful sitcom
from the press this summer. Even the talented Lane and a top-notch
cast (Glenne Headly and Joan Plowright) can't save this
embarrassingly unfunny comedy. What's so shocking is that Encore!
Encore! was created by the same team behind Frasier. Well, they
obviously save all the funny stuff for Kelsey Grammer. Lane (left)
mightily chews the sitcom scenery as a boorish, pompous jerk who
does wacky stuff like pick up fast women and drink mai tais with
his teenage nephew. The problem is, Lane's not a lovable, or even
likable jerk. Just a very obnoxious one.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
