<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TVREVIEW-SPORTS23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sports night
 &HT;    By Kevin D. Thompson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When it debuts: Tuesday, 9:30 p.m., ABC.
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: A behind-the-scenes look at a show that looks a
lot like ESPN's SportsCenter.
</P>
<P>
   How is it? Tries too hard to ape The Larry Sanders Show's witty
and deliciously sarcastic style, but fails. C'mon . . . doesn't
everybody know that sportscasters wear shorts under the desk? More
annoying is Sports Night's schizophrenia. Is it a comedy or is it a
drama? Should we laugh? Or cry? Walking that tightrope isn't wise
since viewers will ultimately get sick of trying to figure it out
and just turn it off. Robert Guillaume, who plays the show's gruff
executive producer, sums up Sports Night best. ``I think this whole
show is going to hell in a hand basket.'' While he was talking
about his fictitious cable show, he could've just as easily been
referring to this witless ABC series.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
