   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ My wife claims she has videotape of it, but I
do not believe her; maybe 8mm movies, that I can believe. We are
talking about possible documentation of something I have tried to
hide for a good while. I'm not proud of it. It is the skeleton in
my closet. Howard Kleinberg is a former editor of the Miami News.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ A friend of mine inspired me in my closet
cleaning duties. She told me of a technique passed on to her by a
friend. You remove every single item from your closet and then put
back only those things you truly love or that look exceptionally
good on you or that fit perfectly. (Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ I have an idea for a
television game show. I'll call it, ``Can You Top This?'' The name
is not new, I confess. It's stolen from an old radio show I used to
listen to when I was a kid. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
