<P>
   CNN-MITCHELL _ ATLANTA _ Pat Mitchell's itinerary calls for her
to spend six whole days at home this month. The president of CNN
Productions is always on the go, from the Sundance Festival to
Castro's office. She's capping a bizarrely eclectic career as a
college teacher, talk show host, ``Today'' substitute for Jane
Pauley, and documentary filmmaker. We catch up with her as her
biggest project ever, CNN's 24-hour ``The Cold War,'' debuts on
Sunday. Profile and biobox. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
