   CMA _Time for the annual telecast of the CMA awards, which
annually wins nightly ratings honors, hosted by Vince Gill. We talk
to Faith Hill, who's up for four awards and leads in total awards
with 17, about public perception of rivalry with Shania Twain, one
nomination. George Strait is top nominee with five and leads
all-time nominees with total of 47. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ENCORE-TVREVIEW _ When it debuts: Tuesday, 8:30 p.m., NBC. What
it's about: A loud-mouthed, self-centered, skirt-chasing opera star
(Nathan Lane) loses his voice and returns to his family-owned
winery in Napa Valley. How is it? It bombs. (Thompson, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TVREVIEW-SPORTS _ When it debuts: Tuesday, 9:30 p.m., ABC. What
it's about: A behind-the-scenes look at a show that looks a lot
like ESPN's SportsCenter. How is it? Tries too hard to ape The
Larry Sanders Show. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TVREVIEW-CLINTON _ It had to be one of the most surreal moments
television has ever produced. A visibly angry, finger-waving
President Clinton answering intimate _ and sometimes salacious _
grand jury questions about his relationship with Monica Lewinsky.
But If viewers were smart, they skipped the four-hour inquisition
and waited for CNN's highlights. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
