   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   BLADDER _MARIETTA, Ga. _ A new treatment developed by a Marietta
company promises to offer an alternative to surgery or urinary pads
for women who suffer incontinence. The Neocontrol Pelvic Floor
Therapy System uses pulsed magnetic therapy to exercise pelvic
muscles that control bladder function. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTO.
</P>
