<P>
   FALL-FASHION-SKIRTS (Undated) Long skirts with sweaters were
epidemic on U.S. and European runways when fall '98 fashions were
unveiled. Show after show opened with a model wearing a slim,
ankle-length or longer skirt topped with one or two sweaters _ big
and bulky, short and tight or perhaps a twinset. And sure enough _
now they're here in stores and on the streets.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FALL-FASHION-HOME (Undated) Fuctional art practically begs to be
included in life because it was created to be beautiful or perhaps
whimsical AND useful _ one-of-a-kind lamps, hand-made rocking
chairs, pottery thrown by an artist and other items are both
user-friendly and affordable.
</P>
<P>
   FALL-FASHION-FABRICS (Undated) Comfortable clothes in luxurious
fabrics set the tone for fall '98. It's the little touches,
however, that make these clothes current and lively, give them
individuality. Here are things to watch to watch for.
</P>
