   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-ECONOMY (Tarrytown, N.Y.) _ In another test of his
international influence, President Clinton meets with Japanese
Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi for a candid discussion about global
and domestic economic issues. Clinton then returns to Washington to
meet with South African President Nelson Mandela. By NANCY MATHIS.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SENATE-BANKRUPTCY (Washington) _ The Senate is expected to pass
a bill making it more difficult to claim bankruptcy and escape
debts, but the legislation faces changes because of a competing
version already approved by the House. By JOHN DRAKE.
</P>
