   CONVERGENCE _ NORCROSS, Ga. _ Convergence Corp., a small private
suburban Atlanta software developer, plays the software game,
turning up a timely product to enhance a new breed of digital cell
phones, as well as the text pagers such as ones now marketed by
BellSouth. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Y2K _ Surprise: Not all Y2K date problems need to be fixed. By
targeting only the critical date operations, a Waltham, Mass.,
company enables its customers to save money and quickly repair
mainframe software. (Chambers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PAXNET _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Nielsen expects to put out
Paxson national numbers today. (Plunkett, Palm Beach Post). 12.
</P>
