</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TV Tonight: Wednesday
 &HT;    By Bob Longino, Phil Kloer, Lyle V. Harris, and Drew Jubera
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   GOOD OLD FAVORITES
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Dharma &AMP; Greg'' 8 p.m. EDT, on ABC _ One of the few new
shows to survive from last season, this sitcom _ starring Jenna
Elfman _raises the ante with baby talk. Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Drew Carey Show'' 9 p.m. EDT, on ABC _ Surprise,
surprise. Drew finds three co-workers have been conspiring to make
his life miserable for years.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``3rd Rock From the Sun'' 9 p.m. EDT, on NBC _ Dick is still
losing his mind. And where's Harry? Our missing extraterrestrial is
in a circus and known as Hargo the Alien.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``NewsRadio'' 9:30 p.m. EDT, on NBC _ The show says goodbye
to Phil Hartman the only way it knows how: by dealing comically
with grief. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Law &AMP; Order'' 10 p.m. EDT, on NBC _ The Emmy-winning drama
starts its ninth season probing an adoption racket. Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   PULL THE PLUG ALREADY
</P>
<P>
   Some tired old shows deserve to die:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Two Guys, a Girl and a Pizza Place'' 8:30 p.m. EDT, on ABC
_ Maybe it's not a real old show, but it sure feels like one.
</P>
