<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, Sept. 23, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   WENATCHEE-FREE (Undated) Idella and Harold Everett, parents of
the two main accusers in the Wenatchee child sex-abuse cases, won't
be re-charged, Chelan County, Wash., Prosecutor Gary Riesen has
told a judge. Riesen reportedly said he won't charge the two, who
had been ordered freed by an appellate court, because the court
didn't throw out the earlier convictions on a basis of law, but
because of misconduct by the invetigator.
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Schneider. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
</P>
