<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sept. 23 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANGELS (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Anaheim Angels host the Texas
Rangers in a battle of the American League West's top two teams.
Texas has a one-game lead with six to play. 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANGELNOTES (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Notebook from the
Angels-Rangers game.
</P>
<P>
   By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MODESTI-COLUMN (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Column from
Angels-Rangers game.
</P>
<P>
   By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   RUN-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Column on Florence Griffith
Joyner.
</P>
<P>
   By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ZEILE (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Feature on Texas Rangers third
baseman Todd Zeile. Zeile is playing with his third team this
season after being traded from Florida and the Dodgers. Zeile
didn't want to leave L.A. because he's a Southern California guy
(Hart High, UCLA) who's very active in charitable works. Despite
his personal upheaval, Zeile has made good on his charity
commitments.
</P>
<P>
   By Eric Noland. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UCLA (Los Angeles) _ Feature on the team's wide-receiver
situation now that Freddie Mitchell has been lost for the season
because of injury. w/8-10 inch sidebar on Hart High's Cody Joyce,
now a freshman at UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   By Jon Wilner. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
