   U.N.-ASSEMBLY (United Nations) _ Moscow is opposed to any
efforts to use outside force to end the war in the Serbian province
of Kosovo, Russia' new foreign minister said on Tuesday in his
first speech to world leaders. By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `i' category.)
</P>
<P>
   NY-BUILDING-INSPECTORS (New York) _ Construction experts say
there are glaring problems with the city's 18-year-old effort to
require inspections and repairs of tall buildings. City officials
acknowledge that laws governing facade maintenance have long
allowed for ineffective, sometimes useless, inspections of many
buildings. And while the officials have made recent efforts to
strengthen the laws, inspection records and interviews with city
officials, engineers, architects and landlords indicate that
numerous problems exist.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 9 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
