<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
PLANES (mjpitzl/tspratt) - Three times in the last month, airplanes
have wandered onto the south runway at Sky Harbor International
Airport in Phoenix at inopportune times - such as when another
plane is about to take off. The latest near-collision happened this
morning, and air-traffic controllers say they could lessen the risk
if the city would change course and pay for warning lights along
the runway. By MARY JO PITZL. Story will move in the ``A``
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
