<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WIRELESS-BELLSOUTH-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Firm gains with phone number portability
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Allegiance Telecom has won an important battle in its
effort to offer competitive local telephone service in metro
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   The Dallas-based telecommunications company can now offer its
customers the ability to keep their old telephone number if they
switch to its service.
</P>
<P>
   In industry jargon, this is called local number portability and
it's considered crucial if competitive carriers are to win
customers from BellSouth. Not only does number portability allow
Allegiance to let people keep their same numbers but it also lets
them offer enhanced services such as caller ID and call forwarding.
</P>
<P>
   ``Having full-fledged permanent local number portability at this
early stage positions Allegiance to take advantage of the
tremendous market opportunity available,'' says Royce Holland,
Allegiance's chairman and chief executive.
</P>
<P>
   Allegiance, which entered the Atlanta market in April, has 530
customers, most of which are small to mid-sized businesses. It has
2,600 local telephone customers nationwide.
</P>
<P>
   Allegiance is one of a dozen-plus carriers who are trying to
compete against BellSouth, a $22 billion telecommunications giant
that dominates the market in the Southeast.
</P>
<P>
   By law, BellSouth must provide local number portability to all
its competitors. But it's a complicated process. In addition, some
carriers such as Allegiance have said that they didn't believe
BellSouth has been as aggressive in providing local number
portability as some other regional telephone companies.
</P>
<P>
   So far, Allegiance and the other competitive carriers haven't
made much of a dent in BellSouth's dominance. BellSouth estimates
it has lost 111,1000 lines _ out of a total of 4.86 million.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
