butternut squash, present variations on this homey classic. (Angel
Franco/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- Sept. 22, 1998 -- NY-WINE-TASTING-2, 9-22 --
No fancy clothes or party manners necessary: taking a break from
errands to sip wine is a growing trend in New York. The city does
not have the vineyards, but it sure has the wine stores, dozens
upon dozens of them, and shrewd customers, after making a few phone
calls and drawing up a little list, can map out a personal wine
trail. (Philip Greenberg/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- Sept. 22, 1998 -- NY-WINE-TASTING-1, 9-22 --
The wine-tasting season is gathering steam after the summer recess.
Eve Strausman and Laurence Green sampling a bottle at Best Cellars,
which holds a free tasting every night. On Saturdays, the store
pairs wine with food. (Boyd Hagen/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- Sept. 22, 1998 -- SPRING-FASHION-2, 9-21 --
Wrapping up a week of earlier showings for spring 1999, American
designers, from marquee names to unknowns, proved with confident
singular collections that they, too, can be trend-setters. From
left, Vivienne Tam's Havana embroidered top, chocolate jams (Corina
Lecca/New York Times Photo); Han Feng's rose draped top and smocked
skirt; Mark Eisen's jersey sweater vest, sweater, sweatpant-style
trousers. (Marilynn K. Yee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- Sept. 22, 1998 -- SPRING-FASHION-1, 9-21 --
The brain transplant that seems to have taken place between Donna
Karan and Helmut Lang is a most startling swap. Ms. Karan has
become the bold experimenter and Lang, the comforting, hard-nosed
realist. From left, Donna Karan's ecru tulle double shell and
jackets over pants (Corina Lecca/New York Times Photo); Helmut
Lang's dress veiled in hot pink with padded shoulder harness
(Marilynn K. Yee/New York Times Photo); Calvin Klein's lithesome
layers of color in green, canary and fire-red silk. (Corina
Lecca/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
